        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-09-12T19:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-09-12T19:20:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <head>30. Circular Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                    to <gloss type="to">Certain Diplomatic Missions Abroad</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d30fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 320/9–1258. Official Use Only; Priority. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_HVF1">Hartley</persName>; initialed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_CWI1">Cargo</persName>; cleared with <gloss target="#t_AF1"
                            >AF</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>, and
                            <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_WFO1">Wilcox</persName> who signed for Dulles. Sent to 48
                        missions worldwide and repeated to Baghdad, Beirut, Khartoum, Jidda, and
                            <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>. Telegram 217, September 12,
                        instructed the <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> to inform the other
                        delegations of continued U.S. support for <persName corresp="#p_MC9"
                            >Malik</persName>. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-09-12T20:20:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1958—8:20 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>267. View current speculation re <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> presidency,
                    Embassy should unless it perceives overriding objections inform Foreign Office
                    soonest at appropriately high level US continues support <persName
                        corresp="#p_MC9">Malik</persName> and hopes other friendly states will take
                    similar position. Embassy should note <persName corresp="#p_MC9"
                        >Malik</persName> candidacy has now been publicly endorsed by Lebanese
                    President-elect. Report reaction soonest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
